            . I am wife of Thomas James; he <rs id="t18280410-207-viclabel1108" type="occupation">keeps a shop</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280410-207-victim1172 t18280410-207-viclabel1108"></join> in <placeName id="t18280410-207-crimeloc1109">Pitfield-street, Hoxton</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280410-207-crimeloc1109" type="placeName" value="Pitfield-street, Hoxton"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280410-207-crimeloc1109" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280410-207-off1106 t18280410-207-crimeloc1109"></join> - On the 12th of March, I was in the parlour and heard money jingle, and presently I heard it again; I then looked towards the shop, and saw something black, which I thought was the dog; but presently I saw a head - I called my husband, who was in bed in the parlour - he went and took the prisoner in the shop. I had seen 3s. 6d. in the till shortly before - I found the till open. and the box containing the silver taken out - I found the money under a mat behind the counter; he had got a knife up his sleeve.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280410-207-person1174">
                  ESTHER 
                  BLATCHLEY
               <interp inst="t18280410-207-person1174" type="surname" value="BLATCHLEY"></interp>
